{
  "stem": "1826.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 225.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1941, I got a, like a vacation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went to a place, Yaremche, the Carpathian mountains.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in June-- I remember the day-- we heard over the radio this speech of Molotov, the Russian minister of foreign affairs, that the Germans attacked Russia.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, we have started a new-- a new face so it was a new-- a new war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I didn't know what to do with myself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I was not in Lemberg, and my brother was in Lemberg.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I tried to-- I tried to get back to Lemberg, and join my brother to evacuate somewhere together.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But when I came to Lemberg, my brother was left already somehow.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I didn't know how-- I didn't-- but he left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] trying to get away too with a-- with a group of friends from that I knew from, from Lodz.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we are supposed to leave, and the authorities all promised now a truck to take us away, to, to Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we came to the spot where the truck was supposed to be, but unfortunately there was no truck.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And anybody who wanted to go away had to go on, on feet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The situation, the, the mood among the Ukrainian population was very anti-Semitic and anti-Soviet.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was afraid to that on the way I'll be killed just, just being a Jew or just running away.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because the Ukrainian population was sympathizing with the-- with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They are [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So unfortunately, I made the wrong decision, and I remained.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remained in Lemberg, and it was the wrong decision.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But, it was like-- and then there I met one who originally came from my-- from the place where I was born.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
